"title": "9220: day of the LORD",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "9220: day of the lord",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The occasion of God's final intervention in human affairs to punish sin, restore the faithful of his people and establish his rule over the nations. It is linked with the Messianic hope and will be fulfilled at Jesus Christ's return. This future consummation is anticipated in historical acts of judgment and, although its time is unknown, it will be heralded and accompanied by signs and by great upheavals in nature.</p>\n<h2>The day of the LORD as a day of judgment</h2>\n<h3>Of universal judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:21-Isa24:22\">ISA 24:21–24:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:14-Zeph1:18\">ZEP 1:14–1:18</a></p>\n<h3>Of judgment on the nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9-Isa13:11\">ISA 13:9–13:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:10\">JER 46:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:28-Job20:29\">JOB 20:28–20:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:4-Isa13:6\">ISA 13:4–13:6</a> <em>God's judgment on Babylon</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:16-Isa19:17\">ISA 19:16–19:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:3-Ezek30:4\">EZK 30:3–30:4</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:1\">ISA 27:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:12-Joel3:14\">JOL 3:12–3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:15\">OBA 1:15</a> <em>God's judgment on Edom</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:8\">ZEP 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:16\">ROM 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:15-Rev6:17\">REV 6:15–6:17</a></p>\n<h3>Of judgment on faithless Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18-Amos5:20\">AMO 5:18–5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:12\">ISA 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:15\">JOL 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:1-Joel2:2\">JOL 2:1–2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:22-Matt7:23\">MAT 7:22–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:48\">JHN 12:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5\">ROM 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>The day of the LORD as a day of hope</h2>\n<h3>A day of restoration for God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:7-Jer30:8\">JER 30:7–30:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:23-Joel2:28\">JOL 2:23–2:28</a></p>\n<h3>God will gather his people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:11\">ISA 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:12-Isa27:13\">ISA 27:12–27:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:6-Mic4:7\">MIC 4:6–4:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:30-Matt24:31\">MAT 24:30–24:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:26-Mark13:27\">MRK 13:26–13:27</a></p>\n<h3>God will save his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:14-Zeph3:20\">ZEP 3:14–3:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa4:5-Isa4:6\">ISA 4:5–4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:1\">ISA 26:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:32\">JOL 2:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:16-Joel3:18\">JOL 3:16–3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:17\">OBA 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:16-Zech9:17\">ZEC 9:16–9:17</a></p>\n<h3>God will purify his people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa4:3-Isa4:4\">ISA 4:3–4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:11-Zeph3:13\">ZEP 3:11–3:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:20-Zech14:21\">ZEC 14:20–14:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:1-Mal4:2\">MAL 4:1–4:2</a></p>\n<h3>God will exalt his people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:21\">OBA 1:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:8\">MIC 4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:8-Mic5:9\">MIC 5:8–5:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:5\">REV 22:5</a></p>\n<h3>God will complete his saving work</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:6\">PHP 1:6</a></strong> <em>The “day of Christ Jesus” is the NT equivalent to the “day of the LORD” which refers to Jesus Christ's second coming.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:1-Dan12:2\">DAN 12:1–12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:40\">JHN 6:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:24\">JHN 11:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:8\">1CO 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:12\">2TI 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>The siege and deliverance of Jerusalem on the day of the LORD</h2>\n<h3>Nations will gather against Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:14-Ezek38:16\">EZK 38:14–38:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:2\">ZEC 14:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:20\">LUK 21:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:8-Rev20:9\">REV 20:8–20:9</a></p>\n<h3>The LORD will fight for Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:18-Ezek38:23\">EZK 38:18–38:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:2-Zech12:5\">ZEC 12:2–12:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:3-Zech14:5\">ZEC 14:3–14:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:12-Zech14:13\">ZEC 14:12–14:13</a></p>\n<h2>The establishment of God's kingdom on the day of the LORD</h2>\n<h3>God's kingdom will be universal and everlasting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:9\">ZEC 14:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:44\">DAN 2:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13-Dan7:14\">DAN 7:13–7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:15\">REV 11:15</a></p>\n<h3>God will be the object of universal worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:19-Isa19:24\">ISA 19:19–19:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:9-Zeph3:10\">ZEP 3:9–3:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:16\">ZEC 14:16</a></p>\n<h3>God's rule will be centred on a restored Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2-Isa2:4\">ISA 2:2–2:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1-Mic4:3\">MIC 4:1–4:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:10-Zech2:12\">ZEC 2:10–2:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:3\">REV 22:3</a></p>\n<h2>The fulfilment of Messianic hope on the day of the LORD</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa4:2\">ISA 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:10\">ISA 11:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:9\">JER 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:5\">HOS 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:11\">AMO 9:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:9\">ZEC 9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:10\">ZEC 12:10</a></p>\n<h2>Being prepared for the day of the Lord</h2>\n<h3>The day will come unexpectedly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:2-1Thess5:3\">1TH 5:2–5:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:43-Matt24:44\">MAT 24:43–24:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:39-Luke12:40\">LUK 12:39–12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32\">MRK 13:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:10\">2PE 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>The need to be ready for the day</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:4-1Thess5:8\">1TH 5:4–5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:5\">EZK 13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:1-Zeph2:3\">ZEP 2:1–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:5\">MAL 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:11-2Pet3:12\">2PE 3:11–3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Signs heralding the day may be discerned</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:33\">MAT 24:33</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:29\">MRK 13:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:31\">LUK 21:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:3\">2TH 2:3</a></p>\n<h2>The day of the Lord will be accompanied by signs and great upheavals in nature</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:19-Acts2:20\">ACT 2:19–2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:30-Joel2:31\">JOL 2:30–2:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9-Isa13:10\">ISA 13:9–13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:10\">JOL 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:11\">LUK 21:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:25-Luke21:26\">LUK 21:25–21:26</a></p>\n<h2>Historical events anticipate the day of the LORD</h2>\n<h3>Disaster foreshadows final judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:29-Isa5:30\">ISA 5:29–5:30</a> <em>Judah invaded by Assyria</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:10\">EZK 30:10</a> <em>Egypt defeated by Nebuchadnezzar</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:2-Joel2:4\">JOL 2:2–2:4</a> <em>Israel devastated by a locust swarm</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:27\">AMO 5:27</a> <em>Israel defeated and exiled by Assyria</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:21\">MAT 24:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:19\">MRK 13:19</a> <em>Jerusalem destroyed by the Romans</em></p>\n<h3>Return from exile foreshadows final restoration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:12-Isa11:14\">ISA 11:12–11:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:23\">HAG 2:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:8\">ZEC 3:8</a></p>",
